cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on enhancing the discriminative capability of deep neural networks for visual pattern classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves introducing multiple classifiers on top of multiple layers, which is related to the design of neural network architectures (cs.NE) and the coordination of multiple agents (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the relationship between the proposed method and classical conditional random fields models, which is a topic in natural language processing and computer vision (cs.CL).
